/#-- vqnewvq.hlp, behind the popup asking for menuitem, description, and 
/#-- tables when creating Append, Browse, or Update type frames.
/#-- 
Enter the menuitem text and a short description of the frame.  For frames 
that query the database, also specify the table(s) you want to use.  

  * The system uses the first 12 characters of the menuitem text to name 
    the frame.
  * Enter a short description.  It will appear throughout your application, 
    wherever a reference to this frame exists.
  * You must designate a Master table for the frame's Visual Query; a
    Detail table is optional.
    - Once you save your specifications, you cannot change the table 
      information.
    - If you make any changes to the underlying structure of your tables, 
      you can use the 'Reconcile' operation under the 'Utilities' menuitem
      to reconcile the Visual Query with the changes.
  * If you do not specify a Detail table, you can have the Master data 
    displayed in either the table field or simple fields format. 
/#subtopic 'Menuitem text' vqnemitx.hlp
/#subtopic 'Description' vqnedesc.hlp
/#subtopic 'Tables' vqnetabl.hlp
